to give up some information.

36:48.166 --> 36:50.633
- [groans softly]
[gate buzzes]

36:52.767 --> 36:55.700
- Hi, Glo.
- Hey.

36:55.767 --> 36:57.633
- I hear you have
William Giles here.

36:57.700 --> 36:59.333
- Yeah, he suffered
a mild heart attack,

36:59.400 --> 37:01.000
so I have him
under observation.

37:01.066 --> 37:02.700
- Is he still talking
in Morse Code?

37:02.767 --> 37:04.266
- Uh-huh.
He seems to do well

37:04.333 --> 37:05.500
with yes and no questions.

37:05.567 --> 37:06.900
- May I?
- Yeah.

37:06.967 --> 37:09.233
- Thanks, Doc.

37:09.300 --> 37:12.333
[machines beeping softly]

37:13.967 --> 37:17.033
[patient coughing]

37:27.000 --> 37:30.967
William, remember me,
Father Mukada?

37:31.033 --> 37:32.433
- Yes.

37:32.500 --> 37:35.066
- How are you feeling?
Better?

37:36.600 --> 37:38.066
- Yes.

37:38.133 --> 37:41.200
- I've been meaning to come
to see you in solitary.

37:41.266 --> 37:45.033
Would you mind
if I asked you a question?

37:45.100 --> 37:47.100
- No.

37:47.166 --> 37:51.367
- You remember 17 years ago
a CO Named Samuel Hughes?

37:51.433 --> 37:54.233
♪ ♪

37:54.300 --> 37:55.567
- Yes.

37:55.633 --> 37:58.900
- You remember that
he was killed here in Oz?

37:58.967 --> 38:00.266
- Yeah.

38:00.333 --> 38:01.567
- Were you there
in the cafeteria

38:01.633 --> 38:04.734
when he was killed?

38:04.800 --> 38:06.100
- Yes.

38:06.166 --> 38:08.567
- You know who killed him?

38:08.633 --> 38:12.100
♪ ♪

38:12.166 --> 38:15.633
Do you know who killed
Samuel Hughes?

38:15.700 --> 38:17.734
- [sighs]

38:19.533 --> 38:22.333
Tell, bye-bye, die.

38:22.400 --> 38:25.567
- No, you won't, I swear.

38:25.633 --> 38:27.033
You'll be back in solitary,

38:27.100 --> 38:30.500
where no inmate can hurt you.

38:30.567 --> 38:31.567
- No.

38:31.633 --> 38:34.233
- There's a young man,

38:34.300 --> 38:36.233
Samuel Hughes' son, Clayton.

38:36.300 --> 38:38.333
He needs to know
what happened to his father.

38:38.400 --> 38:41.166
I've talked to all the other
prisoners who were here then,

38:41.233 --> 38:44.367
and no one will
tell me anything.

38:44.433 --> 38:47.767
William, please?

38:50.433 --> 38:53.166
Which prisoner killed
Samuel Hughes?

38:53.233 --> 38:57.133
♪ ♪

38:57.200 --> 39:00.066
- Uh...

39:00.133 --> 39:02.333
No, no prisoner.

39:02.400 --> 39:05.633
- Not a prisoner?

39:05.700 --> 39:07.734
Then who?

39:15.633 --> 39:17.033
- Leo Glynn.

39:17.100 --> 39:24.133
♪ ♪

39:30.900 --> 39:33.834
- 20, 20,
we got a problem here.

39:33.900 --> 39:35.834
Prisoner's OD'd.

39:35.900 --> 39:38.934
We're too late for the medic.
Send the morgue boys.

39:44.767 --> 39:47.467
[bell ringing]

39:49.066 --> 39:52.000
[tense percussive music]

39:52.066 --> 39:59.100
♪ ♪

40:01.166 --> 40:03.400
- Morning, Len.

40:03.467 --> 40:05.700
- Yeah.

40:07.767 --> 40:10.133
- It's so nice and quiet.

40:10.200 --> 40:12.233
I wish we could
leave 'em like this.

40:12.300 --> 40:14.934
- Especially now,
since Schillinger's son OD'd.

40:15.000 --> 40:16.433
- Yeah, I heard.

40:16.500 --> 40:18.066
I thought Andrew was
in the Hole.

40:18.133 --> 40:20.066
- He was.
- So how did he get the drugs?

40:20.133 --> 40:22.633
- Beats the shit out of me.
- Is Glynn investigating?

40:22.700 --> 40:24.367
- Yeah, but on the QT.

40:24.433 --> 40:26.967
He doesn't seem all
that anxious to find out.

40:27.033 --> 40:28.800
See you tomorrow.

40:39.000 --> 40:40.667
- [sighs]

40:40.734 --> 40:43.667
[bell ringing]

40:43.734 --> 40:46.767
[indistinct chatter]

40:58.133 --> 41:00.333
- How you doing there, Vern?

41:04.467 --> 41:05.967
- [sighs]

41:06.033 --> 41:09.033
I knew a guy,
had one arm.

41:10.066 --> 41:14.367
Told me when he dreams,
he still had both arms.

41:16.200 --> 41:19.266
Every morning, he'd wake up

41:19.333 --> 41:21.166
and have to realize
all over again

41:21.233 --> 41:24.066
one arm was missing.

41:26.266 --> 41:28.867
Every morning, it was like
the first time they told him

41:28.934 --> 41:31.166
his arm was gone.

41:36.333 --> 41:38.166
[sighs]

41:39.633 --> 41:41.867
My son is dead.

41:43.567 --> 41:47.367
- What you did,
getting him the heroin...

41:50.500 --> 41:54.000
That was
the right thing.

41:54.066 --> 41:57.166
Put him to the test.

41:57.233 --> 41:59.867
He was weak.

42:01.233 --> 42:04.667
He was not one of us.

42:04.734 --> 42:06.767
- No.

42:08.000 --> 42:10.834
Way I figure it,
it was euthanasia.

42:13.367 --> 42:16.867
Keller and Beecher
were gonna fuck with my boy.

42:19.367 --> 42:23.100
[sighs]
By killing him...

42:23.166 --> 42:24.200
I saved him.

42:31.633 --> 42:33.700
[sighs]
[buzzer sounds]

42:33.767 --> 42:37.633
- I'm asking McManus
to put me back in your pod.

42:37.700 --> 42:39.433
- Don't.

42:40.800 --> 42:41.900
- Why?
Andy's dead.

42:41.967 --> 42:44.300
He ain't coming
back anytime soon.

42:53.633 --> 42:55.700
You and me,
Beecher.

42:57.233 --> 42:59.567
- Please take
your hand away.

43:01.834 --> 43:03.066
- Beecher.

43:03.133 --> 43:05.567
- Please.

43:05.633 --> 43:08.000
Take your fucking
hand away.

43:09.300 --> 43:11.400
- What the fuck are
you looking at?

43:13.967 --> 43:15.533
You wanted revenge
on Schillinger.

43:15.600 --> 43:17.233
I helped you get that.

43:17.300 --> 43:19.333
[tense music]

43:19.400 --> 43:22.233
- You did it for us?

43:22.300 --> 43:24.166
- Oh, yeah.

43:24.233 --> 43:27.033
- When are you gonna
figure it out?

43:27.100 --> 43:29.667
You and me,

43:29.734 --> 43:32.000
we're never gonna happen.

43:32.066 --> 43:34.834
- You love me, Toby.

43:34.900 --> 43:37.533
- Fuck my ass.

43:37.600 --> 43:44.633
♪ ♪

43:50.400 --> 43:52.300
- Sister Pete.

43:52.367 --> 43:53.633
Hey, I'm gonna see you today.

43:53.700 --> 43:54.934
Right?
- 3:00.

43:55.000 --> 43:56.333
You visiting
one of your ex-wives?

43:56.400 --> 43:58.066
- Yeah.

43:58.133 --> 44:00.333
- Which one,
Kitty or Angelique?

44:00.400 --> 44:02.533
- Bonnie.
Wife number two and number four.

44:02.600 --> 44:05.000
She's the best.
- Mm.

44:05.066 --> 44:07.800
- Hey, there she is,
there she is.

44:07.867 --> 44:10.300
- A-ha, a redhead.

44:10.367 --> 44:12.066
- No, the other one.

44:16.633 --> 44:17.967
- Chris, she's...

44:18.033 --> 44:20.000
- Huge.

44:21.133 --> 44:24.834
- Well, did she gain some
weight after the divorce?

44:24.900 --> 44:27.734
- No, she was that way
when I married her.

44:27.800 --> 44:30.166
Both times.
- Oh.

44:30.233 --> 44:31.934
- Bye.

44:42.166 --> 44:44.266
- You and Schillinger
were together at Lardner

44:44.333 --> 44:46.800
when you were how old?
- 17.

44:48.066 --> 44:50.500
- He saved your life?

44:50.567 --> 44:52.533
- Mm-hmm.

44:53.867 --> 44:55.100
- Did you have
sex together?

44:55.166 --> 44:57.133
- Yeah.

44:57.200 --> 45:00.333
- Did he force himself
on you?

45:00.400 --> 45:02.166
- Vern likes
the power part of sex,

45:02.233 --> 45:05.500
so I let him think
he did.

45:05.567 --> 45:08.033
- You enjoy sex with men?
- I enjoy sex.

45:08.100 --> 45:10.000
Don't you?

45:10.066 --> 45:12.800
You told me you were married
before you became a nun.

45:12.867 --> 45:14.667
You and your husband
have great sex?

45:14.734 --> 45:17.200
- Chris.
- I mean, I can tell you did.

45:17.266 --> 45:19.333
[laughs]
I'll bet you were wild.

45:22.333 --> 45:25.066
Lint.

45:25.133 --> 45:27.600
You miss it, sex?

45:31.834 --> 45:33.967
- I miss my husband.

45:34.033 --> 45:37.000
- Sure.

45:37.066 --> 45:39.934
You ever have sex
with anyone other than him?

45:40.000 --> 45:44.166
- Chris, you know, every time
we have a session together

45:44.233 --> 45:46.200
and we get to a topic
that you want to avoid,

45:46.266 --> 45:49.033
you somehow manage
to turn the discussion

45:49.100 --> 45:51.066
around to me.

45:53.367 --> 45:55.233
- Hmm.

45:55.300 --> 45:59.500
You noticed, huh?
[laughs]

45:59.567 --> 46:01.433
- I just want to get
to the heart

46:01.500 --> 46:04.266
of why you did what you did

46:04.333 --> 46:05.867
to Beecher.

46:07.400 --> 46:10.367
[buzzer sounding]

46:10.433 --> 46:13.633
- You saw my ex, Bonnie.

46:13.700 --> 46:16.967
When I met her,
she was all alone.

46:17.033 --> 46:19.333
Very unhappy.

46:20.867 --> 46:23.867
So I knew it'd be easy
to get her

46:23.934 --> 46:27.667
to fall in love with me.

46:27.734 --> 46:31.333
But what I didn't know

46:31.400 --> 46:33.767
was after I broke her heart...

46:35.767 --> 46:38.567
Would she still love me?

46:41.467 --> 46:44.166
See, I'm a piece of shit.

46:46.400 --> 46:48.967
I...

46:49.033 --> 46:51.333
am worthless.

46:52.567 --> 46:54.834
As bad as they come.

46:57.100 --> 46:59.700
And to have someone
keep loving me

46:59.767 --> 47:02.100
no matter how bad...

47:05.233 --> 47:08.066
You happy now?

47:08.133 --> 47:12.033
You got me to open up and spill
my guts all over your table.

47:16.433 --> 47:19.033
Breakthrough.

47:20.233 --> 47:21.800
- So you went along with Beecher

47:21.867 --> 47:25.300
not in the name
of the Aryan brotherhood...

47:26.300 --> 47:28.867
But to see if he would love you
no matter what?

47:31.266 --> 47:35.367
- At first, I wanted
unconditional surrender...

47:38.834 --> 47:41.600
And then I wanted
unconditional love.

47:45.100 --> 47:47.967
But Beecher don't love me.

47:48.033 --> 47:50.367
- And that's killing you inside.

47:50.433 --> 47:56.834
♪ ♪

47:57.800 --> 47:59.400
- Yeah.

48:00.433 --> 48:07.467
♪ ♪

48:11.500 --> 48:15.700
- [sighs]
Forgive us our trespasses

48:15.767 --> 48:19.233
as we forgive those
who trespass again--

48:19.300 --> 48:22.033
and lead us not into temptation

48:22.100 --> 48:24.400
but deliver us from evil.

48:24.467 --> 48:26.467
For thine is the kingdom...

48:26.533 --> 48:28.667
- Allahu akbar.

48:30.467 --> 48:32.266
Allah.

48:32.333 --> 48:35.333
♪ ♪

48:35.400 --> 48:36.767
Allahu akbar.

48:38.000 --> 48:40.834
[indistinct chatter
and laughter]

48:40.900 --> 48:42.333
This room is reserved.

48:42.400 --> 48:44.633
- I know,
for you Muslims.

48:44.700 --> 48:46.834
- Our daily study group.

48:47.633 --> 48:50.100
Move the chairs.

48:52.233 --> 48:55.200
- I was raised Episcopalian,

48:55.266 --> 48:57.600
which means
we thought about God

48:57.667 --> 49:00.266
once a week for an hour.

49:00.333 --> 49:03.667
But you, you think about him
all the time.

49:07.600 --> 49:08.734
- Yeah.

49:08.800 --> 49:11.433
- Why?

49:11.500 --> 49:13.033
- I want to know him.

49:19.033 --> 49:20.633
- Me, too.

49:23.367 --> 49:26.066
- I wanna know him.

49:26.133 --> 49:28.066
I wanna know God.

49:29.467 --> 49:32.500
I want him to know me,

49:32.567 --> 49:34.767
to know I'm here.

49:36.367 --> 49:38.433
I'm still in this place.

49:40.834 --> 49:42.734
- He knows.

49:43.934 --> 49:46.400
- You know,
when I came to Oz,

49:46.467 --> 49:49.867
I read the Bible
from Genesis to Apocalypse.

49:53.333 --> 49:55.033
- Great book,
the Bible.

49:58.433 --> 50:00.867
May I borrow this?

50:00.934 --> 50:02.734
The Qur'an?

50:02.800 --> 50:07.800
♪ ♪

50:07.867 --> 50:09.533
- Of course.

50:15.567 --> 50:19.934
Beecher...

50:20.000 --> 50:22.700
would you like to stay?

50:22.767 --> 50:25.667
Listen to our discussion?

50:25.734 --> 50:27.300
- Yes.

50:31.133 --> 50:33.300
- Have a seat.

50:33.367 --> 50:36.100
♪ ♪

50:36.166 --> 50:37.900
Come on in,
my brothers.

50:39.700 --> 50:42.133
- What are you doing?
Allowing a non-believer

50:42.200 --> 50:43.600
into our study group?

50:43.667 --> 50:46.400
- A non-believer?

50:46.467 --> 50:48.200
You mean a white man.

50:48.266 --> 50:50.834
- He doesn't belong.

50:50.900 --> 50:53.967
- Beecher is a lost soul

50:54.033 --> 50:56.266
searching for the truth.

50:56.333 --> 50:58.600
He has every right to be there
to receive instruction.

50:58.667 --> 51:01.333
- No.

51:01.400 --> 51:04.133
- No?
- Ever since I came to Oz,

51:04.200 --> 51:07.300
I've listened to you
rationalize your actions.

51:08.533 --> 51:12.734
You are no longer fit
to lead us.

51:12.800 --> 51:14.934
We need an imam
who is above reproach.

51:15.000 --> 51:18.300
- And who's that, Khan?

51:18.367 --> 51:19.767
You?

51:19.834 --> 51:23.400
- Yes.

51:23.467 --> 51:25.066
Never.

51:25.133 --> 51:26.333
[speaking Arabic]

51:26.400 --> 51:29.934
♪ ♪

51:30.000 --> 51:31.567
[speaking Arabic]

51:31.633 --> 51:38.667
♪ ♪

51:49.700 --> 51:52.333
Nacim...

51:52.400 --> 51:54.867
come.

51:54.934 --> 52:01.967
♪ ♪

52:07.533 --> 52:09.100
- [snorts]

52:12.333 --> 52:15.367
[indistinct chatter
and laughter]

52:29.767 --> 52:32.900
- So it's true,
what I heard?

52:32.967 --> 52:34.333
- Yes.

52:42.233 --> 52:44.200
- [sighs]

52:45.934 --> 52:48.734
I still want you
to teach me about God.

52:57.033 --> 52:59.767
- I'm not sure
that I can.

52:59.834 --> 53:06.867
♪ ♪

53:09.266 --> 53:10.533
- Said's out.

53:10.600 --> 53:12.000
- Beecher came to my office,

53:12.066 --> 53:14.934
asked me if he could move
Said into his pod.

53:15.000 --> 53:17.266
- And you said?
- Sure.

53:18.800 --> 53:20.467
- [exhales]

53:20.533 --> 53:21.633
We need to set up
a meeting

53:21.700 --> 53:23.567
with whoever took
Said's place.

53:23.633 --> 53:25.400
What's his name?
- Hamid Khan.

53:25.467 --> 53:28.400
[woman screaming]
- Hey!

53:28.467 --> 53:33.433
♪ ♪

53:33.500 --> 53:34.900
Help!
Help me!

53:34.967 --> 53:37.900
[crying]

53:37.967 --> 53:43.934
♪ ♪

53:44.000 --> 53:46.700
[both grunting]

53:46.767 --> 53:53.800
♪ ♪

53:57.900 --> 54:01.633
[woman crying]
- Prisoner number 9-9-K-5-1-5,

54:01.700 --> 54:03.066
Hamid Khan,

54:03.133 --> 54:05.066
convicted March 6, '99,

54:05.133 --> 54:06.533
aggravated assault.

54:06.600 --> 54:08.033
Sentence: 10 years.

54:08.100 --> 54:10.467
Up for parole in five.

54:14.367 --> 54:17.300
[indistinct chatter
and laughter]

54:17.367 --> 54:24.400
♪ ♪

54:55.233 --> 54:57.667
- Moving in with
the white folk, Kareem?

55:08.633 --> 55:11.133
- Hey, love birds.

55:18.633 --> 55:20.500
- My all-time favorite
punishment?

55:20.567 --> 55:23.100
It's called
Riding the Stang.

55:23.166 --> 55:25.834
The wittiest person in town
would be put on a chair,

55:25.900 --> 55:28.266
carried around the streets
by his fellow townspeople

55:28.333 --> 55:31.367
while he banged on a bucket
and yelled out dirty limericks

55:31.433 --> 55:33.600
condemning the accused.

55:33.667 --> 55:35.767
Being made fun of,

55:35.834 --> 55:39.800
being humiliated in front of
everyone else in your community.

55:39.867 --> 55:42.967
That may be
the cruelest punishment of all.

55:43.033 --> 55:46.066
[breathing heavy]

55:47.133 --> 55:50.166
[Said sobbing]

56:07.767 --> 56:10.800
- No, no.

56:19.066 --> 56:22.100
[sobbing continues]

56:36.934 --> 56:39.867
[tense jazzy music]

56:39.934 --> 56:47.000
♪ ♪

